---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Navigation from '../components/Navigation.astro';
---

<Layout title="Terms of Service - Pragmatic Logic" description="Terms of Service for Pragmatic Logic and Lilo Solace platform usage, including healthcare compliance and service agreements.">
  <Navigation />
  
  <section class="legal-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
      <p class="legal-subtitle">Terms and conditions for using Pragmatic Logic services</p>
      <div class="last-updated">Last Updated: October 6, 2025</div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="legal-content">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="content-wrapper">
        <div class="table-of-contents">
          <h3>Table of Contents</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><a href="#acceptance">Acceptance of Terms</a></li>
            <li><a href="#services">Description of Services</a></li>
            <li><a href="#eligibility">Eligibility and Registration</a></li>
            <li><a href="#healthcare-compliance">Healthcare Compliance</a></li>
            <li><a href="#user-responsibilities">User Responsibilities</a></li>
            <li><a href="#intellectual-property">Intellectual Property</a></li>
            <li><a href="#data-usage">Data Usage and Rights</a></li>
            <li><a href="#service-availability">Service Availability</a></li>
            <li><a href="#limitation-liability">Limitation of Liability</a></li>
            <li><a href="#termination">Termination</a></li>
            <li><a href="#governing-law">Governing Law</a></li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="legal-text">
          <section id="acceptance">
            <h2>1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
            <p>
              These Terms of Service ("Terms") constitute a legally binding agreement between you ("User," "you," or "your") and Pragmatic Logic LLC ("Company," "we," "our," or "us") regarding your use of our website, Lilo Solace platform, and related services (collectively, the "Services").
            </p>
            <p>
              By accessing or using our Services, you acknowledge that you have read, understood, and agree to be bound by these Terms and our Privacy Policy. If you do not agree to these Terms, you must not use our Services.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section id="services">
            <h2>2. Description of Services</h2>
            
            <h3>2.1 Lilo Solace Platform</h3>
            <p>
              Lilo Solace is a multi-agent therapeutic AI platform designed for senior mental health care, featuring:
            </p>
            <ul>
              <li>Seven specialized therapeutic AI agents</li>
              <li>Adaptive wellness monitoring (Cadence Engine)</li>
              <li>Crisis detection and safety assessment</li>
              <li>Family engagement and transparency tools</li>
              <li>Clinical decision support and care coordination</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>2.2 Website and Marketing Services</h3>
            <p>
              Our website provides information about our platform, clinical evidence, demo requests, and customer support resources.
            </p>

            <h3>2.3 Professional Services</h3>
            <p>
              We may provide implementation support, training, clinical consultation, and custom reporting services.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section id="eligibility">
            <h2>3. Eligibility and Registration</h2>
            
            <h3>3.1 Eligibility Requirements</h3>
            <p>You must meet the following requirements to use our Services:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Be at least 18 years of age</li>
              <li>Have legal authority to enter into binding agreements</li>
              <li>Be authorized to act on behalf of your healthcare organization (if applicable)</li>
              <li>Comply with all applicable laws and regulations</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>3.2 Account Registration</h3>
            <p>
              To access certain Services, you must create an account and provide accurate, complete information. You are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of your account credentials and for all activities under your account.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section id="healthcare-compliance">
            <h2>4. Healthcare Compliance</h2>
            
            <h3>4.1 HIPAA Compliance</h3>
            <p>
              For healthcare organizations subject to HIPAA, we will enter into a Business Associate Agreement (BAA) that governs our handling of Protected Health Information (PHI). Our Services are designed to support HIPAA compliance, but ultimate responsibility for compliance remains with the covered entity.
            </p>

            <h3>4.2 Clinical Decision Making</h3>
            <p>
              <strong>Important:</strong> Our AI agents and clinical decision support tools are designed to assist, not replace, professional clinical judgment. All clinical decisions must be made by qualified healthcare professionals. We do not provide medical advice, diagnosis, or treatment.
            </p>

            <h3>4.3 Emergency Situations</h3>
            <p>
              While our platform includes crisis detection capabilities, it should not be relied upon as the sole method for identifying emergency situations. Healthcare facilities must maintain appropriate emergency protocols and professional oversight.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section id="user-responsibilities">
            <h2>5. User Responsibilities</h2>
            
            <h3>5.1 Appropriate Use</h3>
            <p>You agree to use our Services only for their intended purpose and in accordance with:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>These Terms and our Privacy Policy</li>
              <li>All applicable laws and regulations</li>
              <li>Professional standards and ethical guidelines</li>
              <li>Your organization's policies and procedures</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>5.2 Prohibited Activities</h3>
            <p>You may not:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Use the Services for any unlawful or unauthorized purpose</li>
              <li>Attempt to gain unauthorized access to our systems or data</li>
              <li>Interfere with or disrupt the Services or servers</li>
              <li>Reverse engineer, decompile, or disassemble our software</li>
              <li>Share your account credentials with unauthorized persons</li>
              <li>Use the Services to harm, harass, or violate the rights of others</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>5.3 Data Accuracy</h3>
            <p>
              You are responsible for ensuring the accuracy and completeness of all data you input into our Services. Inaccurate data may affect the quality and reliability of our AI recommendations and assessments.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section id="intellectual-property">
            <h2>6. Intellectual Property</h2>
            
            <h3>6.1 Our Intellectual Property</h3>
            <p>
              The Services, including all software, algorithms, content, trademarks, and other intellectual property, are owned by Pragmatic Logic LLC or our licensors. You receive a limited, non-exclusive, non-transferable license to use the Services as permitted by these Terms.
            </p>

            <h3>6.2 Your Data</h3>
            <p>
              You retain ownership of all data you input into our Services. By using our Services, you grant us a limited license to process your data as necessary to provide the Services and as described in our Privacy Policy.
            </p>

            <h3>6.3 Feedback and Suggestions</h3>
            <p>
              Any feedback, suggestions, or ideas you provide about our Services become our property and may be used without compensation or attribution.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section id="data-usage">
            <h2>7. Data Usage and Rights</h2>
            
            <h3>7.1 Data Processing</h3>
            <p>
              We process your data to provide the Services, improve our platform, conduct research, and ensure compliance with legal obligations. All data processing is governed by our Privacy Policy and applicable data protection laws.
            </p>

            <h3>7.2 De-identified Data</h3>
            <p>
              We may use de-identified or aggregated data for research, product development, and benchmarking purposes. Such use complies with HIPAA de-identification standards and does not identify individuals.
            </p>

            <h3>7.3 Data Portability</h3>
            <p>
              Upon request and subject to technical feasibility, we will provide your data in a portable format to facilitate migration to other systems.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section id="service-availability">
            <h2>8. Service Availability and Support</h2>
            
            <h3>8.1 Service Level Commitments</h3>
            <p>
              We strive to maintain high availability of our Services. Specific service level agreements (SLAs) are defined in your separate service agreement or subscription terms.
            </p>

            <h3>8.2 Maintenance and Updates</h3>
            <p>
              We may perform scheduled maintenance and deploy updates to improve our Services. We will provide reasonable notice of planned maintenance that may affect service availability.
            </p>

            <h3>8.3 Support Services</h3>
            <p>
              Technical support is provided according to your service plan. Emergency support for crisis-related issues is available 24/7 for active subscribers.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section id="limitation-liability">
            <h2>9. Limitation of Liability</h2>
            
